### Edge Cases

#### Empty Table
When `issues` is empty:
```
╭─ Issues (0) ────────────────────────────────────────╮
│  No issues found.                                   │
│                                                     │
│  Tip: Create an issue with `br create "Title"`     │
╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯
```

#### Narrow Terminal (< 60 chars)
- Fall back to single-column list view
- Show only ID and truncated title
- Log warning: `warn!(width, "Terminal too narrow for table view")`

#### Very Long Titles (> 100 chars)
- Truncate with ellipsis using existing `truncate_title()` from `src/format/text.rs`

#### Unicode in Titles
- Support full UTF-8 (emoji, CJK, RTL)
- Use `unicode_width` crate for proper column alignment
- Test with: 🔥 火星 العربية

#### Missing Fields
When issue has null/empty fields:
- Show "-" or "(none)" for empty strings
- Show "(unassigned)" for null assignee
- Never panic on missing data

